    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just not that simple. i see them looking at me with so much confusion and stress because of my mistakes. it feels like my presence is just this constant cloud hanging over them. i actually feel like if i wasn't around, they could finally just breathe and be normal kids without the weight of my failures dragging them down. it feels almost selfish to stay when i'm only hurting them.",
